    {
      "sort": 500000,
      "name": "Ninja-Net",
      "type": "text",
      "_id": "GAjZJvKYVBW99twp",
      "system": {},
      "title": {
        "show": true,
        "level": 1
      },
      "image": {},
      "text": {
        "format": 1,
        "content": "<p>NINJA-NET The Ninja Net is a new phenomenon within the world of Naruto, while it may not be wholly canonical for the purpose of this conversion and system, it is a relatively new and novel technology.</p><p>The Ninja-Net, while new is not something that is shared evenly or even distributed freely throughout the Ninja world.</p><p>Ninja net as a concept is basically a collection of data servers that share and communicate information over communication systems such as phone lines or wireless systems such as Bluetooth or radio links.</p><p>For the most part the Ninja-Net has become a global commodity, allowing civilians to purchase food on the net and have it picked up and delivered all without leaving their homes.</p><p>It also gave birth to a set of new potential threats to a village, something called Hackers.</p><p>Hacking has become a new school of focus for Shinobi to excel in, learning how to breach an enemy system and take control, all the while maintain complete anonymity.</p><p>Throughout most of the Ninja world the Ninja net is unique to each country and is broken down into three categories: Regional, National, Militarized.</p><p>The breakdown of these three are as follows;</p><p></p><p>Regional.</p><p>Regional Ninja-Net systems are usually hosts to basic webpages, chat rooms and message boards that primarily connect villagers to one another over relatively long distances of up to 50 Miles.</p><p>Most Regional Ninja-Net systems are powered by newer and more technologically powerful companies and organizations which strive to get their products out to the public via a new sensation called Ads.</p><p>Most of these systems are protected by D and C-Rank security systems.</p><p></p><p>National.</p><p>National Ninja-Net systems are more advanced and far more pretty to look at.</p><p>With national 36 design standards enforced across each nation individually, this is the network that most politicians, including the Kage, use to communicate with other Countries National Ninja-Net systems.</p><p>National Systems are normally limited to the country they are housed under and have to go through dozens of security clearance checks prior to even opening a video call with someone else in another country.</p><p>While these systems are used for international communication, these systems don’t normally hold critical information on it directly, but the security systems in place normally range into the B and A-Rank levels.</p><p></p><p>Militarized.</p><p>The Militarized Ninja-Net are highly advanced systems that keep the entirety of a countries militaries connected.</p><p>These systems are the ones that can spell doom for a squad of shinobi who finds themselves in enemy territory.</p><p>These systems, unlike the previous two can be spread worldwide and localized at the drop of a hat.</p><p>Most of these systems are running due to secretly installed Data Server Scrolls, server terminals that create highly efficient networks that can allow a Shinobi in the Land of Water to communicate with their commanders in the Land of Earth almost instantaneously.</p><p>These systems are mission critical to keep online and usually hold the breath of a countries Secrets, but due to such importance they are usually protected by a series of different S-Rank security measures.</p><p></p><p>Ninja-Net Security.</p><p>The Ninja net for all of its luster is still an exploitable system when challenged by the right tools.</p><p>That’s why most Ninja-Net systems are designed with security systems to protect it, its users, and the files that live on its network.</p><p>When a foreign entity is able to gain access to a network it usually spells doom for that system and any secrets on it.</p><p>So counter hackers or security systems are used to find, punish and eject such entities.</p><p>While a creature is on a network it is not supposed to be on, for every 10 minutes it remains it must make a Check using whatever means it used to gain access to the system vs a Counter Hack DC located on the Ninja Net System Table.</p><p>On a failed check they gain a -2 Penalty to all subsequent checks.</p><p>After 3 failed Counter Hack checks, they are ejected from the system for the next 24 Hours and their physical location becomes known to the system owners.</p><img src=\"systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Cheat%20Sheet/Ninja-Net%20System%20Rank.png\" /><p></p>"
      },
